Quiz 5 - Chapter 9 Control Services and Damemons


Section 9.1 / 9.2: Identify Automatically Started System Processes

Which command shows all active system services on a Linux system?
A) systemctl list-units
B) ps aux
C) top
D) jobs

Which command is used to start a service immediately?
A) systemctl start service_name
B) systemctl enable service_name
C) service service_name status
D) systemctl stop service_name

Which command ensures a service starts automatically at boot?
A) systemctl enable service_name
B) systemctl start service_name
C) systemctl status service_name
D) systemctl disable service_name

Which command stops a currently running service?
A) systemctl stop service_name
B) systemctl disable service_name
C) systemctl start service_name
D) systemctl enable service_name

How can you check if a service is active and running?
A) systemctl status service_name
B) ps aux | grep service_name
C) top
D) jobs

Section 9.3 / 9.4: Control System Services

Which command prevents a service from starting at boot?
A) systemctl disable service_name
B) systemctl stop service_name
C) systemctl mask service_name
D) systemctl enable service_name

What is the purpose of a daemon in Linux?
A) A background process that runs continuously
B) A text editor
C) A foreground application
D) A hardware device

Which command shows all services currently loaded by systemd, regardless of state?
A) systemctl list-unit-files
B) systemctl start service_name
C) systemctl stop service_name
D) systemctl status service_name

Section 9.5 / 9.6: Kill / Restart Services

Which command restarts a running service?
A) systemctl restart service_name
B) systemctl reload service_name
C) systemctl stop service_name
D) systemctl status service_name

True or False: 'systemctl mask service_name' completely prevents a service from being started manually or automatically.
A) True
B) False

---------------------------
Section 9.1 / 9.2: Identify Automatically Started System Processes

systemctl list-units
systemctl start service_name
systemctl enable service_name
systemctl stop service_name
systemctl status service_name

Section 9.3 / 9.4: Control System Services
systemctl disable service_name
A background process that runs continuously (daemon)
systemctl list-unit-files
Section 9.5 / 9.6: Kill / Restart Services
systemctl restart service_name

True (systemctl mask service_name prevents manual or automatic start)


